## Code Review Checklist (apply before completing any task)

- [ ] All functions have type hints and docstrings
- [ ] No magic numbers — constants are named and documented  
- [ ] No mutable default arguments
- [ ] All file paths use `pathlib.Path`, never raw strings
- [ ] Logging added for non-trivial state changes
- [ ] Unit test written for every new pure function
- [ ] Integration test for any new pipeline stage
- [ ] No `print()` statements in non-script code
- [ ] `ruff` + `mypy` pass with zero warnings
- [ ] Large DataFrames use LazyFrame / generators — never `.tolist()` on millions of rows

